# Task
Implement a hero-section-only animated beach backdrop for my portfolio website.

I will provide 2 reference images.
Use them as visual direction only, not as literal assets to copy.

# Core Goal
Create a soft, fresh, energetic summer beach atmosphere for the hero section.

The backdrop should feel:
- clean
- bright
- fresh
- calm
- subtly alive

This is NOT a decorative full-page animation.
This is a restrained background system behind hero content.

---

# Visual Direction

## Camera / perspective
- Straight-on view from the sea looking toward the beach
- The beach sits in the midground
- Distant green mountain range in the background for depth
- Palm / coconut trees placed along the shore
- Sun positioned on the right side of the composition
- Very light clouds, not many

## Mood
- early summer morning
- warm sunlight
- fresh sea breeze
- gentle, relaxing atmosphere
- slightly dreamy but still modern and clean

## Style
- inspired by TanStack wordmark energy:
  - vibrant but controlled gradients
  - clean shapes
  - modern and polished
  - playful but not childish
- avoid realistic cinematic rendering
- avoid noisy textures
- avoid overly saturated neon look
- avoid too many details competing with text

---

# Hero Backdrop Rules

## Scope
- The animated backdrop must exist ONLY inside the hero section
- It must not continue through the whole page
- Content readability has higher priority than visual effects

## Layering
Build the hero using clear visual layers:

1. background sky / mountain image
2. beach + sea base image
3. optional gradient overlay for readability
4. motion layers:
   - soft wave motion
   - subtle tree sway
   - slow cloud drift
   - gentle sun ray shimmer
5. foreground content layer:
   - headline
   - subheadline
   - CTA
   - social links / badges if any

## Readability
- The backdrop must be visually softer than the hero content
- Reduce contrast behind text
- Use blur / haze / translucent overlay if needed
- Never let animation distract from the headline
- Ensure the text remains readable on desktop and mobile

---

# Motion Design Principles

## General motion philosophy
All animations must be subtle, slow, and layered.
The user should "feel" motion before they consciously notice it.

Avoid:
- fast movement
- large amplitude motion
- looping that feels obvious
- dramatic parallax
- aggressive glow
- constant attention-seeking motion

Use:
- low amplitude
- slow timing
- staggered loops
- slightly different durations
- slight opacity changes
- soft easing

---

# Required Animations

## 1. Waves
Goal:
- gentle wave wash near the shore
- chill and relaxing
- not stormy
- not cartoon bouncing

Implementation direction:
- animate only the shoreline / water highlight / wave edge
- use slow horizontal and vertical distortion
- tiny amplitude
- layered wave movement is preferred over one obvious repeated wave

Suggested behavior:
- 2 to 3 wave layers
- each layer moves at slightly different speed
- motion should feel like soft water breathing
- foam edge can shift subtly left-right and in-out

Animation feeling:
- 5s to 10s loop range
- ease-in-out
- no sharp repetition

## 2. Tree sway
Goal:
- light summer breeze moving through the palms
- the trees should feel alive, not bending dramatically

Implementation direction:
- only animate upper leaves / crowns, not whole trunks swinging heavily
- use small rotational movement
- slight independent motion per tree
- do not sync all trees perfectly

Animation feeling:
- 3deg to 6deg max rotation
- slow staggered loops
- around 4s to 8s
- very soft ease

## 3. Clouds
Goal:
- a few clouds drifting lightly
- sparse cloud composition
- preserve open sky feeling

Implementation direction:
- only 2 to 4 cloud groups max
- move slowly across the sky
- slight opacity variation is okay
- scale drift is optional but minimal

Animation feeling:
- very slow, almost imperceptible
- 20s to 60s loop range
- clouds should not dominate composition

## 4. Sun rays / sunlight shimmer
Goal:
- sunlight gently shining from the right side
- warm and soft, not dramatic god rays
- subtle glow on sea surface and air

Implementation direction:
- use faint radial gradient or blurred light beams
- apply very soft opacity pulse
- optional shimmer reflection on water near right side
- keep it elegant and restrained

Animation feeling:
- ultra subtle
- 6s to 12s slow pulse
- very low opacity changes

