---

# Technical Constraints

## Performance
This hero must feel lightweight.

Prefer:
- CSS transforms
- opacity animation
- GPU-friendly properties
- layered divs / SVG / pseudo-elements
- minimal JS
- requestAnimationFrame only if truly needed

Avoid:
- heavy canvas rendering unless justified
- expensive blur on huge full-screen moving layers
- large JS animation libraries if CSS can handle it
- overly complex particle systems

## Responsiveness
The hero must remain visually good on:
- desktop
- tablet
- mobile

On smaller screens:
- reduce visual complexity
- reduce number of animated layers
- keep hero text area clean
- ensure the sun / mountain / shoreline composition still feels balanced

## Accessibility
- respect prefers-reduced-motion
- if reduced motion is enabled:
  - keep only static backdrop
  - or dramatically reduce all animation amplitudes and durations

---

# Implementation Guidance

## Preferred architecture
Create a dedicated component, for example:
- `HeroBackdrop.tsx`
or
- `HeroScene.vue`

Separate responsibilities:
- `HeroBackdrop`
- `WaveLayer`
- `CloudLayer`
- `SunGlowLayer`
- `PalmMotionLayer`

## Styling approach
Use layered absolute-positioned elements inside the hero container.
The hero section should be `position: relative; overflow: hidden;`.

Recommended structure:
- hero wrapper
- backdrop base image layer
- animated overlays
- readability gradient / blur veil
- content container with higher z-index

## Suggested rendering strategy
If using provided artwork:
- set the artwork as the primary background visual
- augment life through overlays instead of trying to redraw the whole scene

Possible techniques:
- background image + animated gradient overlays
- SVG wave masks
- CSS keyframes for palm sway
- drifting cloud divs / SVG assets
- radial gradient for sun glow
- translucent blur overlay under content area

---

# Motion Tuning Requirements
Before finalizing, tune motion so that:
- the user notices the text first
- the motion feels premium, not playful-demo-like
- nothing flickers
- the loop seams are hard to notice
- the whole scene feels calm and breathable

If the motion feels obvious within 2 seconds, it is too strong.
Reduce amplitude, contrast, or speed.

